{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.30",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 30,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 30",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 30 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:1",
      "text": "“But now they make sport of me, men who are younger than I, whose fathers I would have disdained to set with the dogs of my flock.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:2",
      "text": "What could I gain from the strength of their hands, men whose vigor is gone?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:3",
      "text": "Through want and hard hunger they gnaw the dry and desolate ground;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:4",
      "text": "they pick mallow and the leaves of bushes, and to warm themselves the roots of the broom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:5",
      "text": "They are driven out from among men; they shout after them as after a thief.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:6",
      "text": "In the gullies of the torrents they must dwell, in holes of the earth and of the rocks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:7",
      "text": "Among the bushes they bray; under the nettles they huddle together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:8",
      "text": "A senseless, a disreputable brood, they have been whipped out of the land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:9",
      "text": "“And now I have become their song, I am a byword to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:10",
      "text": "They abhor me, they keep aloof from me; they do not hesitate to spit at the sight of me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:11",
      "text": "Because God has loosed my cord and humbled me, they have cast off restraint in my presence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:12",
      "text": "On my right hand the rabble rise, they drive me forth, they cast up against me their ways of destruction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:13",
      "text": "They break up my path, they promote my calamity; no one restrains them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:14",
      "text": "As through a wide breach they come; amid the crash they roll on.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:15",
      "text": "Terrors are turned upon me; my honor is pursued as by the wind, and my prosperity has passed away like a cloud.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:16",
      "text": "“And now my soul is poured out within me; days of affliction have taken hold of me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:17",
      "text": "The night racks my bones, and the pain that gnaws me takes no rest.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:18",
      "text": "With violence it seizes my garment; it binds me about like the collar of my tunic.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:19",
      "text": "God has cast me into the mire, and I have become like dust and ashes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:20",
      "text": "I cry to thee and thou dost not answer me; I stand, and thou dost not heed me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:21",
      "text": "Thou hast turned cruel to me; with the might of thy hand thou dost persecute me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:22",
      "text": "Thou liftest me up on the wind, thou makest me ride on it, and thou tossest me about in the roar of the storm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:23",
      "text": "Yea, I know that thou wilt bring me to death, and to the house appointed for all living.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:24",
      "text": "“Yet does not one in a heap of ruins stretch out his hand, and in his disaster cry for help?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:25",
      "text": "Did not I weep for him whose day was hard? Was not my soul grieved for the poor?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:26",
      "text": "But when I looked for good, evil came; and when I waited for light, darkness came.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:27",
      "text": "My heart is in turmoil, and is never still; days of affliction come to meet me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:28",
      "text": "I go about blackened, but not by the sun; I stand up in the assembly, and cry for help.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:29",
      "text": "I am a brother of jackals, and a companion of ostriches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:30",
      "text": "My skin turns black and falls from me, and my bones burn with heat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.30.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 30:31",
      "text": "My lyre is turned to mourning, and my pipe to the voice of those who weep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
